sect1.para:
JAX-RPC uses the Java Beans Activation framework to support various MIME content
            types. The WSDL/XML to Java mapping in JAX-RPC will map the status
            part defined above to an instance of javax.activation.DataHandler
            whose content is of type org.jvnet.fastinfoset.FastInfosetSource.
            Thus, the return statement of the addPhoto operation would create
            an instance of DataHandler as shown below.
                Fast Infoset Attachments in Java
                        public javax.activation.DataHandler addPhoto(...)
            throws java.rmi.RemoteException 
        {
            ...
            return new DataHandler(
                new FastInfosetSource(...), "application/fastinfoset");
        }
